cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper deals with improving the performance of natural language processing (NLP) applications using post-processing techniques applied to word embeddings. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes new methods for post-processing, which involves learning orthogonal latent variables from ordered input sequences, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Learning). Additionally, the paper applies these techniques to two popular word embedding methods, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with improving the performance of NLP applications, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as word embeddings are often used in image captioning and other computer vision tasks.
